verbose_text: Using data pooled from the three populations and after correcting for age and sex, angiogenin levels were significantly lower in ALS patients than in controls in plasma / serum (mean +/- SD = 438.2 +/-112.2 ng/ml for the ALS group and 467.6 +/-105.4 ng/ml for controls; p = 0.001, Mann-Whitney-Wilcoxon test) and in CSF (mean +/- SD = 5.582 +/-1.754 ng/ml for the ALS group and 6.197 +/-1.987 ng/ml for controls; p = 0.01, Mann-Whitney-Wilcoxon test).
